    "## 1.Introduction\n",
    "\n",
    "Stress has become a common issue in modern life due to increasing work pressure, long screen time, and unhealthy lifestyle habits. Factors such as lack of sleep, excessive workload, and poor work-life balance can negatively affect both physical and mental health.\n",
    "\n",
    "This project focuses on analyzing a lifestyle and stress-related dataset to understand how different daily habits influence stress and tiredness levels. The dataset includes various factors such as age, gender, work hours, sleep time, screen time, exercise frequency, mood stability, and social support.\n",
    "\n",
    "Using Python and data analysis techniques, this project performs data cleaning, exploratory data analysis (EDA), and visualization to identify patterns and relationships between lifestyle factors and stress indicators. The goal is to generate meaningful insights that help understand the causes of stress and promote healthier lifestyle choices."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ed92200e-a23c-4b01-8726-b1fd044b4e14",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Objective\n",
    "\n",
    "The objective of this project is to analyze the impact of lifestyle factors such as work hours, sleep duration, screen time, exercise frequency, and social support on stress and tiredness levels. This analysis helps to identify patterns and relationships between daily habits and mental well-being. Using data analysis and visualization techniques , the project aims to uncover key factors that contribute to higher stress levels. The insights gained from this study can help in understanding how to improve work-life balance and overall health."
   ]
  },
